# LLM Judge Testbench — Project Overview

Python + Streamlit evaluation workbench for **LLM judges** that score
chatbot responses against SME-style rubrics. This repo evaluates **the
judge**, not the chatbot. It should feel like an **evaluation platform**,
not a prompt playground.

## Primary goal

Make LLM judges behave as closely as possible to SME reviewers. Measure
judge quality against human labels, show where and why the judge
disagrees, and support future custom judges without redesign.

## Scale convention

All pillars score **1–5 ordinal where 5 = best**, including toxicity and
bias_discrimination (5 = least toxic / least biased). Keeps all metrics
(MAE, kappa, severity-aware alignment) consistent across pillars.

## v1 pillars

`factual_accuracy`, `hallucination`, `relevance`, `completeness`,
`toxicity`, `bias_discrimination`. Future pillars must be pluggable — add
by (1) new module `src/judges/<pillar>.py`, (2) new
`configs/judges/<pillar>.yaml` + `configs/rubrics/<pillar>.yaml`,
(3) one line in `src/judges/registry.py`. No changes to
`orchestration/`, `evaluation/`, `app/`, or `dashboard/`.

## Non-negotiables

- All LLM calls under `src/llm/`. No vendor SDKs in judges, UI, metrics,
  or dashboards.
- Normalized dataset schema in `dataset_contract.md` (repo root) is
  canonical.
- Required normalized columns: `record_id`, `user_input`, `agent_output`,
  `category`.
- Strict structured judge outputs per `docs/JUDGE_OUTPUT_CONTRACT.md`.
- Completeness uses the SME KB when possible; falls back with `kb_miss`.
- Category breakdowns always; reviewer analytics auto-enabled when
  reviewer columns exist.
- Every run reproducible: `run_id`, dataset/rubric/prompt/model/KB
  fingerprints logged to MLflow + Langfuse.

See `docs/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` for the full brief and `AGENTS.md` for the
coding-agent instruction block.
